    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When everything's nearly ready, add your <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>red chilli relish</strong> to a<strong> </strong>small bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and gradually stir in<strong> </strong>80ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [110ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [130ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>(this is to ensure there's no lumps!) – this is your <strong>sweet chilli mix</strong></p><p>Put the <strong>sweet chilli</strong> <strong>mix</strong> in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until thickened, stirring half way, then add the <strong>diced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave the fresh chilli!</span></strong></p>",
